[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/overcalls"]
[Student "S"]
{EAST has a 19 point balanced hand, including a stop in \Hs. 
He plans to double, then bid NT. (see Deal 9)

WEST has 10 points though, so he jumps to 2\S. 

In theory EAST could now bid 2NT to continue the description of his hand, but he might as well 
go ahead and bid 3NT instead.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "E:97.QJT9.954.KQ65 AQT53.64.QT.A974 86.K732.A876.T83 KJ42.A85.KJ32.J2"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "4S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
1H 1S pass 3S pass 4S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: S, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 0, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "f3eb1307f86e36c8fceec662f922f893947b83e9b689a14ff7b476563069a980"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/overcalls"]
[Student "S"]
{With a 5-card \S suit and 13 points SOUTH should overcall 1\S.

NORTH has 13 points and four \Ss. If SOUTH had opened, NORTH's hand would be good enough 
to insist on game. But since SOUTH overcalled, NORTH merely invites with a jump to 3\S.

SOUTH has better than a minimum overcall so she accepts the invitation and bids 4\S.}

